line_1: The others sportful the brisk vintage quaff.
line_2: With that he brast into a scornful laugh,

line_1: Each silvery Flower the streams aerial quaff,
line_2: Bow her sweet head, and infant Harvest laugh.

line_1: Surrounding Gods the circling nectar quaff,
line_2: Gaze on the Fair, and envy as they laugh.

line_1: Their mingling gore the Fiends of Vengeance quaff,
line_2: And Hell receives them with convulsive laugh.

line_1: Or with the merry fellows quaff,
line_2: And laugh aloud with them that laugh;

line_1: Else might we quiet sit and quaff,
line_2: And gently chat, and gayly laugh

line_1: And in dire banquets the warm life-blood quaff;
line_2: The mangled heads! — o'er which they sing and laugh,
